oracle.adf.view.faces.bi
Interface BIFacesConstants

Deprecated. No replacement 

public interface BIFacesConstants

This class contains constants used for sending events from the client to the server. Applications developers do not need to use this interface.

Since:
4.0
For internal use only. Application developers should not use this

ROTATE_EVENT

static final java.lang.String ROTATE_EVENT
Deprecated. 
JSF event: Rotate. This event is generated and handled by BI JSF Componenents.

This event has the following parameters:

  • ORIGIN
  • TO + ORIGIN
  • FROM + ORIGIN
  • OPERATION + ORIGIN

The literal value of ROTATE_EVENT is "bi_rotate".

See Also:
Constant Field Values

LAYOUT_EVENT

static final java.lang.String LAYOUT_EVENT
Deprecated. 
See Also:
Constant Field Values

FROM

static final java.lang.String FROM
Deprecated. 
JSF event parameter: From. This is a parameter of the ROTATE_EVENT. This parameter identifies one or the other of the following:
  • One of two edges to swap -- In the URL, this will appear as a one-character representation of DataDirector.COLUMN_EDGE, DataDirector.ROW_EDGE, or DataDirector.PAGE_EDGE.
  • A dimension (layer) to move to or to swap with another location -- In the URL, the first character is used by the Rotate tool internally, and the rest of the string is the name of the dimension.

The literal value of FROM is "bi_from".

See Also:
Constant Field Values

TO

static final java.lang.String TO
Deprecated. 
JSF event parameter: To. This is a parameter of the ROTATE_EVENT. This parameter identifies one of the following:
  • An edge that should be swapped with another edge -- In the URL, this will appear as a one-character representation of DataDirector.COLUMN_EDGE, DataDirector.ROW_EDGE, or DataDirector.PAGE_EDGE.
  • A dimension (layer) to swap with another dimension (layer) -- In the URL, the first character is used by the Rotate tool internally, and the rest of the string is the name of the dimension.
  • A location before or after a particular dimension, to which the FROM dimension should be moved -- In the URL, the first character is a representation of either MOVE_BEFORE or MOVE_AFTER. The rest of the string is the name of the dimenson.

The literal value of TO is "bi_to".

See Also:
MOVE_BEFORE, MOVE_AFTER, DataDirector.COLUMN_EDGE, DataDirector.ROW_EDGE, DataDirector.PAGE_EDGE, Constant Field Values

The literal value of OPERATION is "bi_op".

REQUIRED_SELECTION_FOR_ENABLING_CUSTOM_CONTEXT_MENU_ITEM

static final java.lang.String REQUIRED_SELECTION_FOR_ENABLING_CUSTOM_CONTEXT_MENU_ITEM
Deprecated. 
When a java.util.String[] of information regarding which context menu items to include for the UIExplorerTree or UIExplorerTable is being created, REQUIRED_SELECTION_FOR_ENABLING_CUSTOM_CONTEXT_MENU_ITEM should be used to specify what types of selection should cause this menu item to be enabled. The value that is passed in for this parameter has to be a vector of types. If the vector of types contains the String "any", the menu item is enabled as long as something is selected. If the vector of types contains PSRConstants.FOLDER, the menu item will be enabled when a folder is selected. If the vector of types contains "document", the menu item will be enabled as long as the item selected is anything other than a folder. If the vector of types contains other types (instead of "document") then the menuitem will only be enabled for those types. If this parameter is not set at all, the menu item is always enabled.

See Also:
